  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6767.66 sitting right in the thick negative gamma zone between 6750-6760 (-54.7B to -46.4B), dealers are aggressively buying this rally as they're caught short gamma in a BREAKOUT regime. The recent wall break and GEX surge (76.5% 1-min change) confirms dealers are scrambling to hedge, creating amplified buying pressure that should continue pushing SPX toward the 6800 positive gamma wall where selling pressure will emerge. Watch for potential reversal/resistance at 6800 (+46B) as dealers flip to selling, but any dip back toward 6750-6760 will trigger aggressive dealer buying again.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect continued upside momentum toward 6800 with strong buying support on any dips to 6750.",
